# GitHub Package Registry Configuration
# 
# To use packages published to GitHub Package Registry:
# 1. Copy this file to .npmrc
# 2. Replace YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME with your actual GitHub username
# 3. Create a personal access token with `read:packages` scope
# 4. Set the token as NPM_TOKEN environment variable

@YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME:registry=https://npm.pkg.github.com
//npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${NPM_TOKEN}

# For CI/CD environments, you can use GITHUB_TOKEN:
# //npm.pkg.github.com/:_authToken=${GITHUB_TOKEN}
